content.description:
Scramble up the chimney, beside "Avis".  Once past the crux of "Avis" you can step across to the big ledge, then head up the crack left of the corner.  Alternatively, keep going up the chimney. 

  There is a fair amount of loose rock on and around this route - make sure your belayer is in a safe location!
content.location: The chimney on the left end of the formation

content.description: Up the center of the blank face, to the big ledge:  crimp, huck, jug.  Finish as for "Avis".
content.protection: Not much chance of gear on this one.
content.location: The face in the center of U-Haul Overhangs.

content.description:
A rewards program for loyal customers. 

  The start involves some devious side-pulls, passing within a hair of "Hurts", then diverging left onto some fun jug-hauling.
content.location: Just to the left of "Hurts" - for some moves, just inches away.

content.description: Climb the broken overhanging crack just a few feet left of Budget, resisting the urge to bail onto that climb.  Though it is short, this climb packs quite a punch, and Swartling's 5.8 rating feels like a hefty sandbag.  It seems like very solid 5.9.
content.protection: Standard rack, safe by DL standards.
content.location: This is right in the middle of the U-Haul Overhang, just to the left of Budget.

content.description: A fun romp up 2" wide edges.  Swartling & Mayer describe some contrived 5.7 start, but if you are leading, the obvious place to begin is the crack system at the right end of the formation.  Continue up edges on the east facing wall, near the edge.  At the top, add some more free mileage by shifting right to the crack before topping out.
content.protection: The key is small stuff in the horizontals.
content.location: At the extreme right end of the formation

content.description: Nice hand crack with face holds.
content.location: West side of U-Haul Overhangs. Right of two cracks a few feet apart.

content.description: Scramble up the chimney, then find your way to the bottom of the crack on the left side of the central face.  Once on the big ledge, continue angling up and right through the break in the overhangs.
content.protection: Gear to 2".  You could use one big piece at the bottom to protect the opening moves, and you'll want a smaller cam for the business.
content.location: Left side of the face, to the right of the chimney.

pathTokens: East Bluff 02 - East of the Quarry

content.description: A compact little crag. Every route on it's south face is overhung, and jugs abound. The closest thing around here to jug-hauling .
